What is Linux?
Linux is an open-source, Unix-like operating system kernel used in servers, desktops, and embedded systems.

Difference between Linux and Unix?
Linux is open source and free; Unix is mostly proprietary and paid.

What is a kernel?
The kernel is the core of the OS that manages CPU, memory, and hardware.

What is the shell?
The shell is a command-line interface that allows users to interact with the OS.

Popular Linux distributions?
Ubuntu, CentOS, RHEL, Debian, SUSE.
